    {
      "id": 17,
      "documentId": "hne6kdkc57n09otr2itdbtjs",
      "title": "Sustainable Farming Practices in Western Kenya",
      "slug": "sustainable-farming-practices-in-western-kenya",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Trans Nzoia County, often called Kenya's breadbasket, is home to thousands of smallholder farmers who are now embracing sustainable agricultural practices. These methods not only protect the environment but also improve crop yields and farmer incomes.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Climate-smart agriculture techniques being adopted include crop rotation, organic composting, water conservation through drip irrigation, and agroforestry — planting trees alongside crops to improve soil health and provide shade.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "AgroDakk Foods works directly with 50+ farming families in the region, providing training on these sustainable methods. Farmers who implement these practices typically see a 30-40% increase in vegetable yields within two growing seasons.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Our model ensures that farmers are paid fair prices for their produce while maintaining strict quality standards. This approach creates a sustainable cycle: healthy soils produce better vegetables, which command higher prices, which allows farmers to invest back into their land.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "publishedDate": "2026-04-16",
      "excerpt": "How smallholder farmers in Trans Nzoia County are adopting climate-smart agriculture to increase yields while protecting the environment.",
      "author": "Mary Wanjiku",
      "featured": true,
      "createdAt": "2026-06-14T12:32:14.145Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-06-28T08:51:56.796Z",
      "publishedAt": "2026-06-28T08:51:56.852Z",
